OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FParents of sudden-death    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchildren 'let down by NHS' 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The NHS is failing some parents whose  
OL,6, children die unexpectedly, a leading   
OL,7, paediatrician has told BBC Panorama.   
OL,9,FAbout 50 children's deaths in the UK   
OL,10,Fevery year are termed as "sudden       
OL,11,Funexplained death in childhood" (SUDC).
OL,12,FLittle is known about what causes them.
OL,14,FSome bereaved families get none of the 
OL,15,Fsupport they're entitled to, setting   
OL,16,Fthem up for "a lifetime of misery",    
OL,17,Fsays Dr Joanna Garstang.               
OL,19,FThe NHS says it "offers bereaved       
OL,20,Ffamilies a range of support".          
